import pandas as pd
import nltk
from textblob import TextBlob
from transformers import pipeline
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

nltk.download('vader_lexicon')
from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer

# Load your dataset
df = pd.read_csv("final_cleaned_english_only.csv")
df = df[df['cleaned'].notna() & (df['cleaned'].str.strip() != "")]
sample_df = df.sample(n=10000, random_state=42).copy()  # adjust sample size as needed

In [3]:
theme_keywords = {
    "Accommodation": ["kitchen", "parking", "tidy", "spacious", "organized", "view", "cleanliness", "comfort"],
    "Host Experience": ["host", "responsive", "helpful", "hospitality"],
    "Service/Communication": ["communication", "review"],
    "Location/Travel": ["santa monica", "pier", "venice", "california", "attractions", "location", "quiet"],
    "Pet-Friendliness": ["dogs", "pets", "barking"],
    "Comfort/Ambience": ["cozy", "peaceful", "clean", "calm", "homely"],
    "Guest Feedback": ["5 stars", "recommend", "rating", "future", "enjoyment", "satisfaction"]
}

def assign_theme(text):
    text = text.lower()
    for theme, keywords in theme_keywords.items():
        if any(k in text for k in keywords):
            return theme
    return "Uncategorized"

sample_df['theme'] = sample_df['cleaned'].apply(assign_theme)
In [5]:
vader = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()
sample_df['vader_score'] = sample_df['cleaned'].apply(lambda x: vader.polarity_scores(x)['compound'])

def label_sentiment(score):
    if score >= 0.05: return "positive"
    elif score <= -0.05: return "negative"
    else: return "neutral"

sample_df['vader_label'] = sample_df['vader_score'].apply(label_sentiment)
In [7]:
sample_df['textblob_polarity'] = sample_df['cleaned'].apply(lambda x: TextBlob(x).sentiment.polarity)
sample_df['textblob_label'] = sample_df['textblob_polarity'].apply(label_sentiment)
In [9]:
bert = pipeline("text-classification", model="nlptown/bert-base-multilingual-uncased-sentiment")

def get_bert_sentiment(text):
    try:
        label = bert(text)[0]['label']
        if "1" in label or "2" in label: return "negative"
        elif "3" in label: return "neutral"
        else: return "positive"
    except: return "error"

sample_df['bert_sentiment'] = sample_df['cleaned'].apply(get_bert_sentiment)

In [11]:
bart = pipeline("zero-shot-classification", model="facebook/bart-large-mnli")

def get_bart_sentiment(text):
    labels = ["positive", "negative", "neutral"]
    try:
        return bart(text, labels)['labels'][0]
    except: return "error"

sample_df['bart_sentiment'] = sample_df['cleaned'].apply(get_bart_sentiment)

Device set to use mps:0
In [13]:
t5 = pipeline("summarization", model="t5-small", tokenizer="t5-small")

def get_t5_summary(text):
    prompt = f"What is the sentiment of this review? {text}"
    try:
        return t5(prompt, max_length=50, min_length=10, do_sample=False)[0]['summary_text']
    except:
        return "Error"

sample_df['t5_summary'] = sample_df['cleaned'].apply(get_t5_summary)

# Score the summary
def get_t5_polarity(text):
    if text != "Error":
        return TextBlob(text).sentiment.polarity
    return None

sample_df['t5_polarity'] = sample_df['t5_summary'].apply(get_t5_polarity)
sample_df['t5_sentiment'] = sample_df['t5_polarity'].apply(label_sentiment)

# Load models
bart = pipeline("zero-shot-classification", model="facebook/bart-large-mnli")
bert = pipeline("text-classification", model="nlptown/bert-base-multilingual-uncased-sentiment")
t5 = pipeline("summarization", model="t5-small", tokenizer="t5-small")

In [69]:
def get_bart_sentiment(text):
    labels = ["positive", "neutral", "negative"]
    try:
        return bart(text, candidate_labels=labels)['labels'][0]
    except:
        return "error"

def get_bert_sentiment(text):
    try:
        label = bert(text)[0]['label']
        if "1" in label or "2" in label:
            return "negative"
        elif "3" in label:
            return "neutral"
        else:
            return "positive"
    except:
        return "error"

def get_t5_sentiment(text):
    try:
        prompt = f"What is the sentiment of this review? {text}"
        summary = t5(prompt, max_length=50, min_length=10, do_sample=False)[0]['summary_text']
        polarity = TextBlob(summary).sentiment.polarity
        if polarity >= 0.05:
            return "positive"
        elif polarity <= -0.05:
            return "negative"
        else:
            return "neutral"
    except:
        return "error"

In [73]:
sentiment_models = ['bart_sentiment', 'bert_sentiment', 't5_sentiment']
accuracy_results = {}

for model in sentiment_models:
    matches = human_df[model] == human_df['Human_Label']
    accuracy = matches.sum() / len(matches)
    accuracy_results[model] = round(accuracy * 100, 2)

accuracy_df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(accuracy_results, orient='index', columns=['Accuracy (%)'])
accuracy_df = accuracy_df.sort_values(by='Accuracy (%)', ascending=False)
print(accuracy_df)

                Accuracy (%)
bart_sentiment          79.0
bert_sentiment          75.0
t5_sentiment            29.5
In [75]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

accuracy_df.plot(kind='bar', color='teal', title="Model Accuracy vs Human Labels", legend=False)
plt.ylabel("Accuracy (%)")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
